#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1431
msgid "Expanded Sequence of Play"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1432
msgid ""
"<i><strong>This is NOT meant to be used in normal game play.</strong> "
"This is meant to resolve any disputes or confusion integrating all rules "
"from the base game [b]and all three expan­sions[/b]. It is meant to be a "
"final arbiter on any possible confusion. Honestly, you will probably "
"never need this, but it is here if you do.<i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1433
msgid "<strong>1. Determine Player Order (first turn of the game only)</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1434
msgid "<strong>2. Turn One:</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1435
msgid "<strong>Player 1:</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1436
msgid "<strong> a. Movement.</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1437
msgid "<strong> b. Combat.</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1438
msgid ""
"<strong> c. Exploration.</strong> Note that if Exploration results in "
"hostile forces in the same hex return to Step b. immediately and resolve "
"the combat now."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1439
msgid "<strong>Player(s) 2-8:</strong> Same as Player 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1440
msgid "After all players have had a turn any Doomsday Machines on the map move."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1441
msgid "<strong>3. Turn Two:</strong> Same as turn one."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1442
msgid "<strong>4. Turn Three:</strong> Same as turn one."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1443
msgid ""
"<strong>5. Economic Phase</strong> – All players conduct this phase "
"simultaneously, not in player order. Exception to that is Resource Cards,"
" which are played at the Start of the Economic Phase in Reverse Player "
"Order."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1444
msgid "<strong>MOVEMENT</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1445
msgid ""
"Units may move from one hex to another at up to the maximum speed they "
"are equipped with. This movement may be increased by MS Pipelines or "
"Black Hole Slingshots, but not both. This movement may be reduced by "
"entering various terrain types, hexes that contain enemy units, and hexes"
" that are beside enemy units equipped with <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Advanced Comm Array [g][#28][/g]</span>. Ships use "
"Exploration technology before moving. One or more Resource Cards may be "
"played after Exploration tech is used but before any ship movement."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1446
msgid ""
"<strong>Raiders vs. Scanners:</strong> When the attacker moves into a hex"
" with enemy units and the attacker has Raiders present that they wish to "
"continue moving, the following happens. (Note that though these rules "
"refer to Raiders, they also cover any other ships equipped with "
"Cloaking.)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1447
msgid "• The attacker states that they have Raiders and want to continue moving."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1448
msgid ""
"• The defender states that they have Scanner 1 (and the attacker must "
"stop) or that they lack Scanner 1 (and the attacker may continue moving)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1449
msgid ""
"• If the defender stated that they had Scanner 1 the attacker may declare"
" Cloaking 2."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1450
msgid ""
"• The defender states that they have Scanner 2 (and that the attacker "
"must stop) or that they lack Scanner 2 (and the attacker may continue "
"moving)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1451
msgid ""
"The defender has the option of not announcing their Scanner level and "
"allowing the Raiders to continue to move. Tech levels must be announced "
"in combat (See Step C8), but combat has not been declared at this point."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1452
msgid ""
"<strong>Black Hole Survival Checks:</strong> These happen before Reaction"
" Movement is declared and before non-combat ships are destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1453
msgid ""
"A ship with <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Advanced Comm Array "
"[g][#28][/g]</span> cannot React into a black hole hex if the enemy ship "
"is attempting a Black Hole Slingshot. That ship can still React to the "
"next hex the enemy ship enters, if that hex is adjacent to the ship "
"making the Reaction Movement."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1454
msgid ""
"If the attacker uses the Black Hole Slingshot rule to move to another hex"
" any non-combat ships are destroyed before the attacking ships leave."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1455
msgid "<strong>NON-COMBAT SHIPS SPECIAL MOVEMENT RULES</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1456
msgid ""
"Units without an Attack Strength may not enter hexes that contain enemy "
"units, enemy Colonies, or face-down System markers unless a friendly "
"combat- capable ship also enters the hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1457
msgid ""
"Units without an Attack Strength are destroyed if caught alone in a hex "
"by combat-capable enemy units. No information about the enemy units is "
"revealed by this except for the fact that they are armed. There are two "
"exceptions to this rule:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1458
msgid ""
"• Units without an Attack Strength are not destroyed if they are in a "
"Black Hole hex and all of the enemy units fail their Black Hole survival "
"checks."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1459
msgid ""
"• Units without an Attack Strength and not in a Black Hole hex are not "
"destroyed if friendly combat-capable units declare that they will use "
"<span class=\"text-uppercase\">Advanced Comm Array [g][#28][/g]</span> to"
" React into the hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1460
msgid "<strong>COMBAT</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1461
msgid "<strong>C1</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1462
msgid ""
"Combat-capable units or Colonies from two opposing sides are in the same "
"hex after a player has finished moving."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1463
msgid "<strong>C2</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1464
msgid ""
"Defender may move ships by Reaction Movement if they have the technology "
"needed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1465
msgid "<strong>C3</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1466
msgid "• Attacker declares whether they have Cloaking 1 or not."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1467
msgid "• Defender declares whether they have Scanner 1 or not."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1468
msgid ""
"• If defender has Scanner 1, attacker declares if they have Cloaking 2 or"
" not."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1469
msgid ""
"• If attacker declared they have Cloaking 2, then defender declares if "
"they have Scanner 2 or not."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1470
msgid "<strong>C4</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1471
msgid "• Defender declares whether they have Cloaking 1 or not."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1472
msgid "• Attacker declares that they have Scanner 1 or not."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1473
msgid ""
"• If attacker has Scanner 1, defender declares if they have Cloaking 2 or"
" not."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1474
msgid ""
"• If defender declared they have Cloaking 2 then attacker declares if "
"they have Scanner 2 or not."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1475
msgid "<strong>C5</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1476
msgid ""
"Play Resource cards that are played before ships are revealed (<span "
"class=\"text-uppercase\">Missed Rendezvous [g][#84][/g]</span>, <span "
"class=\"text-uppercase\">Retreat When Engaged [g][#107][/g]</span>, and "
"<span class=\"text-uppercase\">Alien Reinforcements [g][#90][/g]</span>)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1477
msgid ""
"<strong>Raiders and <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Missed Rendezvous "
"[g][#84][/g]</span>:</strong> If <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Missed "
"Rendezvous [g][#84][/g]</span> causes a situation in which there are no "
"ships equipped with Scanner until Round 2, there are three possibilities:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1478
msgid ""
"1. If the Raider side has nothing but Raiders and they are trying to "
"avoid combat by staying cloaked after learning this, then the battle does"
" not start until the Scanner-equipped ship arrives and Round 2 will count"
" as Round 1 for most purposes. The Raiders will still be able to retreat "
"at the first D-Class firing opportunity they get."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1479
msgid ""
"2. If the Raider side has Raiders that are trying to avoid combat by "
"staying cloaked AND ships that are not Raiders, then Round 1 is fought as"
" normal, but the Raiders cannot fire or be fired at. In Round 2, the "
"Raiders can be fired at and can retreat or fire at the first D-Class "
"firing opportunity they get."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1480
msgid ""
"3. If the Raiders declare that they want the +1 in Round 1, then Round 1 "
"is fought as normal. The Raiders will fire as A-Class Units with a +1 to "
"their Attack Strength. In Round 2, the Raiders will be treated as D-Class"
" Units."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1481
msgid "<strong>C6</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1482
msgid ""
"Reveal ship types and numbers. Attacker first and then the defender. At "
"this point, if a Colony is present the defender must state which of their"
" Ground Units are on the Colony and which are on Transports."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1483
msgid "<strong>C7</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1484
msgid ""
"Attacking Raiders that have not had their cloak nullified may retreat. "
"Defending Raiders that have not had their cloak nullified may retreat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1485
msgid "<strong>C8</strong>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1486
msgid ""
"Both sides reveal what tech is on their units and some Empire Advantages "
"and Alien Technology Cards are revealed. Both sides reveal the Experience"
" levels that their units have."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1487
msgid ""
"All special abilities that Unique Ships and Advanced Flagships mount must"
" be revealed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1488
msgid ""
"Ground 2, Terraforming 1-2, and Military Academy 1 are not revealed in "
"space combat. All other technology is revealed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1489
msgid "The following Alien Tech Cards must be revealed if a unit mounts them:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/competitive_scenario_book.py:1490
msgid ""
"[g][#2][/g], [g][#3][/g], [g][#5][/g], [g][#10][/g], [g][#11][/g], "
"[g][#12][/g], [g][#13][/g], [g][#14][/g], [g][#15][/g], [g][#16][/g], "
"[g][#22][/g], [g][#24][/g], [g][#25][/g], [g][#26][/g], [g][#27][/g]*, "
"[g][#28][/g], [g][#29][/g], [g][#30][/g], [g][#56][/g], [g][#183][/g], "
"[g][#185][/g], [g][#186][/g], [g][#282][/g], [g][#283][/g]."
